ess, she opens up exciting new lines of inquiry in the fields of law, politics, and gender studies. Law in Crisis represents a promising new development in the interdisciplinary study of law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aLawxPhilosophy. 0aLawxPolitical aspects. 0aNatural disastersxLaw and legislation. 0aSubjectivity. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804772426zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804772426423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804772426.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles